other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
other_tests.findings: Gallbladder is distended and contains several peripherally calcified gallstones, none of which appear to be impacted within the gallbladder neck. A sliver of fluid or gallbladder wall edema is seen along the liver margin. The liver enhances normally without focal concerning lesion. The common bile duct appears normal in caliber.
